    <mods:abstract>
        Between the late 1950s and early 1980s, approximately 20,000 Indigenous, Métis, and Inuit
        children accross Canada were taken from their families by Child Welfare Services 
        to be put into foster care or adopted by White families. The practice was intentional
        and systematic. The resulting disconnect of the children from their heritage has 
        been called "cultural genocide."
    </mods:abstract>
